Enable TCP access from trusted network

cidr.description: CIDR range for the VPC CIDR block

contact_email.description: Contact email for the team or individual creating the resources

create_vpc.description: Controls if VPC should be created (it affects almost all resources)

created_by.description: Name of the person or identity that created the resource

default_security_group_egress.description: List of maps of egress rules to set on the default security group

default_security_group_ingress.description: List of maps of ingress rules to set on the default security group

enable_dns_hostnames.description: Should be true to enable DNS hostnames in the VPC

enable_dns_support.description: Should be true to enable DNS support in the VPC

environment.description: Environment to be deployed. Must be one of: prod, dev, or stage.

iam_role_tags.description: Additional tags to attach to the EC2 IAM role

instance_profile_tags.description: Additional tags to attach to the Instance Profile

instance_tags.description: Additional tags to attach to the EC2 instance

instance_type.description: EC2 instance type to use for the firewall

internet_gateway_tags.description: Additional tags to attach to the internet gateway

key_name.description: The name for the key pair. Conflicts with `key_name_prefix`

launch_template_tags.description: Additional tags to attach to the launch template

namespace.description: Namespace to identify the provisioned resources. Can be an app name, etc...

prefix.description: The pre-fix to attach to created resources.

private_eni_tags.description: Additional tags to attach to the private ENI

private_route_table_tags.description: Additional tags for the private route table

private_subnet_suffix.description: Prefix to attach to private subnets

private_subnet_tags.description: Additional tags for the private subnets

public_eni_tags.description: Additional tags to attach to the public ENI

public_subnet_suffix.description: Prefix to attach to public subnets

public_subnet_tags.description: Additional tags for the public subnets

region.description: AWS Region in which to deploy the firewall

size.description: Size of the firewall to deploy

suffix.description: Suffix to attach to created resources

tags.description: A map of tags to add to all resources

team.description: The name of the team provisioning the resource

vpc_prefix.description: Pre-fix to attach to created VPC resources

key_pair_fingerprint.description: The MD5 public key fingerprint as specified in section 4 of RFC 4716

private_key_id.description: Unique identifier for this resource: hexadecimal representation of the SHA1 checksum of the resource

private_key_openssh.description: Private key data in OpenSSH PEM (RFC 4716) format

private_key_pem.description: Private key data in PEM (RFC 1421) format

public_key_fingerprint_md5.description: The fingerprint of the public key data in OpenSSH MD5 hash format, e.g. `aa:bb:cc:....` Only available if the selected private key format is compatible, similarly to `public_key_openssh` and the ECDSA P224 limitations

public_key_fingerprint_sha256.description: The fingerprint of the public key data in OpenSSH SHA256 hash format, e.g. `SHA256:....` Only available if the selected private key format is compatible, similarly to `public_key_openssh` and the ECDSA P224 limitations

public_key_openssh.description: The public key data in "Authorized Keys" format. This is populated only if the configured private key is supported: this includes all `RSA` and `ED25519` keys

public_key_pem.description: Public key data in PEM (RFC 1421) format

create.description: Determines whether resources will be created (affects all resources)

create_private_key.description: Determines whether a private key will be created

key_name.description: The name for the key pair. Conflicts with `key_name_prefix`

key_name_prefix.description: Creates a unique name beginning with the specified prefix. Conflicts with `key_name`

private_key_algorithm.description: Name of the algorithm to use when generating the private key. Currently-supported values are `RSA` and `ED25519`

private_key_rsa_bits.description: When algorithm is `RSA`, the size of the generated RSA key, in bits (default: `4096`)

tags.description: A map of tags to add to all resources
